<TITLE> 27 BNP leaders, activists held in Sherpur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sherpur, Nov 21 (bdnews24.com)  Police arrested 27 local BNP leaders and activists in Sherpur on Saturday on charges of disturbing the peace. The arrestees claimed they were detained "for no reason" while they were leaving the home of former whip Zahed Ali in Nakla after a meeting. Nakla police chief AKM Fosiur Rahman told bdnews24.com the local leaders of BNP and its student wing Jatiyatabadi Chhatra Dal men had been arrested at around 2am for "creating panic among the public". Sherpur district BNP convener AKM Saiful Islam Kalam claimed angrily, "The arrests were just for harassment". He told bdnews24.com they were holding a meeting to settle an internal dispute among local BNP leaders. Kalam demanded immediate release of the arrested. Police said a case was underway. bdnews
